\viewkind4\uc1\pard\ltrpar\cf1\b\f0\fs20 In this example, data and files from the server will be synchronized to the client:\par
\par
* Files (such as images) are synchronized using the \cf2 ServerFileToClient()\cf1  function.\par
\pard\ltrpar\sb100\sa100 * Data is synchronized using the \cf2 DataViewToDataSource()\cf1  function.\par
\par
After running the first synchronization, only the modified records will be copied from the server to the client.\par
You can change a record on the server DS, change another record on the local DS and run the sync process and see that the modified server record is now updated to the local data but the modified local record was not changed.\par
}
